<!DOCTYPE document PUBLIC "-//APACHE//DTD Documentation V2.0//EN" "http://forrest.apache.org/dtd/document-v20.dtd">

<document>
  <header>
    <title>hcatalog/queue/:id </title>
  </header>

  <body>
  <section>
   <title>Description</title>
    <p>Check the status of or kill jobs created by Templeton.  Substitute ":id" with
     the job ID you received when the job was created.</p>
  </section>

  <section>
   <title>Usage</title>
    <p><code>POST /v1/hcatalog/queue/:id.json</code></p>
    <p><code>POST /v1/hcatalog/queue/:id.json?op="kill"</code></p>
  </section>

  <section>
   <title>Parameters</title>
    <table>
    <tr><th>Name</th><th>Description</th><th>Required?</th><th>Default</th></tr>
    
    <tr><td><strong>op</strong></td>
        <td>Either "status" to get the current job status or "kill" to 
           kill the job.</td>
        <td>Optional</td>
        <td>status</td>
    </tr>
    </table>
  </section>

  <section>
   <title>Results</title>
     <p>Returns the json object:</p>
     <p><code> {"result": MESSAGE, "status": STATUS} </code></p>
     <p>Where MESSAGE is a string similar to "ok", and STATUS is a string 
        containg the current job status, for example 
        "completed", "error", or "running".</p>    
 </section> 
 </body>
</document>
